<!--==Summer days and frost days==
<br><br>
A summer day is defined as a day where the daily maximum temperature exceeds 25&deg;C. Figure 6 shows the number of summer days for 2017 as a deviation from the 1981-2010 long-term average.
<br><br>
A frost day is a day where the daily minimum temperature drops below 0&deg;C. This temperature is usually reached during the night-time, see Figure 7.
